postcontent: LWRC REPR (Rapid Engagement Precision Rifle) .308/7.62NATO, semi-auto, 18" barrel, 1:10 twist, chrome bore, short stroke gas piston, Geiselle 2-stage trigger, nickel boron coated BCG, Surefire muzzle brake, Magpul PRS stock, 4 (four) 10-round magazines, mounted with a Nightforce NXS 5.5-22x50 MLR long range mildot scope, illuminated reticle with LaRue QD rings. Will provide the operation manual for the scope. Sorry, but I'm retaining the sling, case and bipod seen in the photos. This gun has proven extremely reliable and accurate for me, but son's college has become the driving factor. Less than 950-rounds count. There is a little sign of use at the charging handle (of course), and on the 4-magazines. Otherwise it is essentially unblemished. Excellent condition for a used gun. (And for those of you with a good eye, yes the LaRue QD rings were mounted on the opposite side, to avoid catching your hand when operating the charging handle - but you're welcome to change it when you buy).

title: For Sale:  KelTec Shotgun NEW IN BOX - $1,050 as pictured/$900 stock
postcontent:
The KSG is Kel-Tec's first entry into the shotgun market.  The size, shape and design are similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward.  The KSG weighs 6.9lbs and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1" overall length and an 18.5" cylinder bore barrel.  Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 14 rounds of 12 gage 2-3/4" rounds (7 per tube).  The simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube.  The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.  The lever can be positioned in the center detent in order to easily clear the chamber without feeding another round from either magazine.  A cross bolt style safety blocks the sear, and the pump release lever is located in front of the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under Picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, or a light or laser.  The included top Picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights.  Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included.  The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

I have added sights and Sun Optic grip with light and green laser. Also a limb saver recoil pad. $1,050 with these options. $900 without. FIRM
